The paper discusses the concept of human-agent teaming, which involves the interaction between humans and intelligent machines. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science. 

Firstly, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the design of new human-machine interaction concepts. 

Secondly, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the use of intelligent systems in human-agent teaming. 

Thirdly, cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper discusses the technical architecture supporting social human-agent teaming. 

Fourthly, cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is another possible category as the paper discusses the interaction between humans and machines as equal team partners. 

Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper discusses the social aspects of human-agent teaming.
